    <text id="B0554T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How reports on the condition of medical affairs in his district.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bu. R. F. &amp; A. L.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr><lb/>Richmond, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-01-10"><abbr expan="January">Jany</abbr> 10th 1866</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Respecting medical affairs in this District there is no material change since my
                    last report. I do not learn that there has been any marked increase in sickness
                    or mortality. There still exists the want of a medical officer to look on the
                    field and see that proper care and attention are given by those selected to
                    attend the poor freedmen.</p>

                <p>I forward herewith two bills for services which I think to be fair and just, and
                    respectfully ask that they may be approved, and ordered to be paid by me.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed/>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
